  "text": "The role of deep venous reflux in the pathogenesis of varicose veins of the lower extremities is unclear. In a study by Almgren et al [CITATION_1] in 1989, incidence of deep venous insufficiency in patients with recurrent or residual varicose veins was as high as 42.9%. In the same study they found that after age 60 years, 42% of the patients with varicose veins had deep venous reflux, compared with 19% of patients younger than 29 years.",
